    # game/areas/galerocks02npcs.rpy:205
    old "“Is that what your life is about? Excitement?” He doesn’t give you time to answer. “In {color=#f6d6bd}Gale Rocks{/color}, we do what we have to, not what we want. We support each other and our families, resting in winter, if at all. No matter how wounded or disfigured one is, we’ll spend our days caring for them,” he points at his scarred neck, then shows you his left hand. One finger and a half are already gone. “I’m proud of such a home, I am. Your paths are twisted.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks02npcs.rpy:213
    old "He scoffs. “No traveler knows a real trade. Once you get back to the city, try to carry crates and barrels day after day, for five years straight. You’ll understand what it means to live like other people do, no matter if they want to or not.” "
