    # game/areas/galerocks02npcs.rpy:241
    old "You explain briefly how it would work. “Aw right, I see. Like the tribe of {color=#f6d6bd}Creeks{/color} does? We’d rather stick to what we have, stranger. These {i}traps{/i} are fragile, and the sea is harsh. They would get crushed by tides, or broken by big fish and birds. Nets are already a big help, we used to have only spear hunters.” He gives you an unusually warm smile. “I appreciate the thought, but fishing is in our blood. We know what we’re doing, we do.” "
