    old "She puts away her tools, leans away, and meets your eyes. “You try to hire her for something, alright? She’s {i}difficult{/i}. Taught herself lies said with a strong voice and confident chest can take one far, but that ain’t a good path in a tribe. Like all souls she has good sides and bad sides, but is too afraid to admit the latter.” \n\nYou chat for a few more minutes. While the tailor’s words are harsh, she can’t hide the sadness of her voice. "
