    # game/areas/galerocks02npcs.rpy:5247
    old "“Ehm, I ain’t leaving a stranger behind,” she states matter-of-factly. “Either speak while I listen, or not at all.” \n\nYou end up in a chamber that doesn’t stand out from all the others. It has a lit candle inside, and two shapes among the furs, one of them covered with a blanket. You see the movement of their breathing shells, but the elders don’t react to your arrival, and you’re not sure if they are conscious. \n\n“{color=#f6d6bd}Vita{/color}, {color=#f6d6bd}Valerius{/color}. This roadwarden came to see you,” says {color=#f6d6bd}your guide{/color}, then takes a step back. \n\n{color=#f6d6bd}The man{/color} raises his head slowly and puts weight on his elbows. He’s skinny, covered with brown dots, sparse hair, and isn’t as stooped as his companion, who most likely wouldn’t be able to get up on her own. “A warden? Not {color=#f6d6bd}Glaucia{/color}?” "
